model_explanation: S1 says Sam only gave Bill bananas, which excludes that he gave Bill grapes. So S2 directly contradicts S1.
the subject and object pairs are completely different. S1 is about Sam and Bill with bananas, and S2 is about Sam and Mary with apples, so they are independent.
S1 only restricts what Sam gave to Bill, but it says nothing about what Sam gave to Ellen, so S1 and S2 do not affect each other and are independent.
S1 claims only Sue got apples from Sam, which excludes that Tom was also given apples, so S2 contradicts S1.
if Sam only gave Bill grapes, that means Sam did not give Bill any other fruit, including oranges, which means S2 is entailed by S1.
if Sam only gave Bill apples, then Sam did not give Bill bananas, so S2 is entailed by S1.
according to S1, Sue only received apples from Sam, which means Sue did not receive bananas, so S2 is entailed by S1.
S1 only refers to what was given to Ellen. It does not mention what Sam gave or didn’t give to Tom, so S2 is independent of S1.
S1 restricts Sam’s giving of apples to Tom only, but says nothing directly about Mary. While it might suggest Mary didn’t get apples, it’s not stated explicitly in S1, so S2 is independent.
S1 says Tom is the only person who received apples from Sam, which excludes Bill getting apples as well. Thus, S2 contradicts S1.
